Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over half the @Cajun spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and fry, stirring, until soft and slightly charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and remaining Cajun spice mix to the pepper. Stir well and fry for ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour in the @sweetcorn{150%g} and the liquid from the tin.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @tomato ketchup{1} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @soured cream{75%g} and lime zest. Set aside.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #board{} and chop into 1cm pieces.

Pop the avocado into another small bowl. Squeeze over half the lime juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine, then set aside.

When your sauce has thickened, remove the pan from the heat.

Squeeze in the remaining lime juice and stir to combine. Taste the sauce and add more salt and pepper if needed.

Share the wedges between your plates, then top with the corn and pepper mixture.

Spoon over the avocado and top with dollops of the zesty soured cream.

Sprinkle over the grated cheese to finish.

Enjoy!